    {
      "type": "eq",
      "start": 62,
      "end": 78,
      "html": "<section class=\"slide eq\"><ul class=\"eq-lines\"><li id=\"imp89sfou36\" class=\" eq-item eq-title \" > Newton's Second Law </li><li id=\"imp89sfou37\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ F = ma $$ </li><li id=\"imp89sfou38\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ F = 2 \\times 3 $$ </li><li id=\"imp89sfou39\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ F = 6 $$ </li></ul><div class=\"eq-side-panel\"><div id=\"imp89sfou36-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"eq.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfou36-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Force depends on mass and acceleration. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou37-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > F means force. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou37-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > m means mass. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou37-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > a means acceleration. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou37-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > This is one of the most important physics equations. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou37-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Greater acceleration requires greater force. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou37-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Heavy objects resist motion changes. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou38-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"box.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfou38-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Substitute values into the formula. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou39-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The resulting force equals 6 newtons. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou39-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Units matter in physics. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou39-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Always include measurement units. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou39-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Physics combines math with reality. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou39-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Equations describe natural behavior. </div><div id=\"imp89sfou39-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Reasoning matters more than memorization. </div></div></section>",
